OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 24 Jun to Fri 3 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure is expected to be
OL,7,Fdominant at the start of the period,
OL,8,Fwhich will bring predominantly fine
OL,9,Fand dry conditions with temperatures
OL,10,Fwell above normal, albeit with a small
OL,11,Frisk of a few showers or thunderstorms
OL,12,Fat times. Into the the last weekend of
OL,13,FJune, an area of low pressure may
OL,14,Ftrack to the west of the UK, which
OL,15,Fbrings the potential for notably hot
OL,16,Fconditions to build from the south
OL,17,Fagain, alongside a risk of thundery
OL,18,Foutbreaks. By early July it remains
OL,19,Ffinely balanced as to whether low
OL,20,Fpressure, and more changeable
OL,21,Fconditions, are allowed to take over,
OL,22,For whether the more settled conditions
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fhold sway.
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1781876894
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 4 Jul to Sat 18 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure patterns are slightly
OL,7,Fmore likely than low pressure patterns
OL,8,Fduring this period, meaning settled
OL,9,Fand drier than average conditions are
OL,10,Fmost probable. However, there is still
OL,11,Fa chance of some changeable, more
OL,12,Funsettled conditions could develop at
OL,13,Ftimes, and a risk of some heavy and
OL,14,Fthundery showers. Temperatures are
OL,15,Flikely to be above normal, with a
OL,16,Fgreater than normal chance of hot
OL,17,Fconditions developing.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
